summary: This is an AT&T International Call Detail Record (ICDR) report listing 66 phone calls from July 6, 2019, to August 11, 2019. The report was run on August 15, 2019, and shows calls originating from and dialed to various countries, including the USA, Switzerland, France, the UK, Belarus, Russia, and others. It appears to be a log of phone activity for a specific SIM card, likely obtained as part of an investigation.

events.title: Phone Activity Period
events.description: A series of 66 international phone calls were made and received on a specific SIM card, as logged by AT&T.

keyFacts: The document is an AT&T International Call Detail Record (ICDR) report run on August 15, 2019, covering calls from July 6 to August 11, 2019.
The call log shows frequent international calls involving countries such as the USA, Switzerland (abbreviated 'switz'), France ('frnce'), the UK ('uk'), Belarus ('blrus'), and Russia ('russa').
Many calls are short (0:00-0:30 duration), but several have longer durations, such as a 14:51 minute call from the UK to the USA on July 8 and a 5:08 minute call from the USA to Belarus on August 10.
The originating and dialed country codes indicate a pattern of calls between the USA and Eastern European countries (Belarus, Russia) during this period.
The document is marked as proprietary and for use by authorized persons only, indicating it was likely obtained via legal process for an investigation.
